  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining Room Details**\n\nI\'ve been examining the `Room` interface and how it uses `Record<string, string>` for the `details` property. My focus has been understanding the rationale behind this design choice, considering its implications for how information is structured and stored within the application. I\'m thinking about the types of detail pairs expected, and how they would be used.\n\n\n**Analyzing Output Token Usage**\n\nI\'m now investigating the excessive 334KB output size. I\'ve pinpointed `responseSchema: worldSchema` and `responseMimeType: \"application/json\"` as potential culprits, suspecting a runaway process filling the `description` field. My current hypothesis centers on the `description` field within `worldSchema` as a point of optimization. I\'m going to set `maxOutputTokens` to 2048 to manage output length. I\'ve considered that there might be an issue with nested schemas but didn\'t find anything significant.\n\n\n**Refining Output Control**\n\nI\'m now implementing strategies to constrain output size. I plan to refine the `details` schema to use an array of objects. I\'ll add `maxOutputTokens` to the configuration, introduce explicit prompt limits to reduce verbosity, and include a JSON repair utility. I\'m examining `aiService.ts` to integrate these changes, and will revise `monsterSchema` and `roomSchema` to strengthen robustness.\n\n\n**Examining Data Schema**\n\nI\'m now diving into the `loot` definition and its use of `itemSchema`, defined at line 21. Also, I\'m re-evaluating the `initializeGame` function. My focus is on model selection; I\'ve decided to lean towards `gemini-3.1-pro-preview` for world generation because of its reliability for schema-driven tasks, although I may use `gemini-3-flash-preview` for speedier results. Currently, the code uses an older model. I\'ve also drafted a more robust `detailSchema` using key-value pairs and am checking how the current `responseSchema` handles null values.\n\n\n**Implementing JSON Repair**\n\nI\'m now integrating a `cleanAndParseJson` function into `aiService.ts` to improve JSON parsing. This includes code to strip markdown code blocks and attempt basic repairs on malformed JSON to increase robustness. I\'m focusing on handling partially closed strings, and missing braces or brackets.\n\n\n**Adjusting Output Length**\n\nI\'ve discovered the root cause of the JSON size issue: model hallucinations leading to very large outputs. Setting `maxOutputTokens` to 4096 should help, and I\'ll refine the prompt for length control. I\'m preparing to edit `services/aiService.ts` and will implement the robust JSON parsing in `processPlayerTurn`. I also need to verify that `gemini-2.5-flash` isn\'t a typo for `gemini-3-flash-preview`.\n\n\n**Confirming Model Usage**\n\nI\'m now changing model names. I see that the code currently uses `gemini-2.5-flash` in several places. I will update these to `gemini-3-flash-preview` for quick tasks and `gemini-3.1-pro-preview` for the `initializeGame` and `processPlayerTurn` functions, which need robust schema handling. I\'m prioritizing accuracy for critical tasks.\n\n\n**Verifying Schema Nuances**\n\nI\'m now investigating the interplay of nullability with the `Type.OBJECT` construct, focusing on whether a simple spread operator is sufficient for handling optional nested objects. I\'ve re-examined the `roomSchema` and will implement a safer method if necessary, especially with regards to null checks. I\'ll add validation for the `details` conversion.\n\n\n"
    tool_calls {
      id: "49911c2b-9e3e-4fe0-9122-fe5146f26aee"
      name: "multi_edit_file"
      arguments_json: "{\"Instruction\":\"Improve JSON parsing robustness, add maxOutputTokens, fix details schema, and update model names to recommended versions.\",\"ReplacementChunks\":[{\"ReplacementContent\":\"const detailSchema = {\\n    type: Type.OBJECT,\\n    properties: {\\n        key: { type: Type.STRING, description: \\\"The keyword for the detail (e.g., \'altar\', \'painting\').\\\" },\\n        value: { type: Type.STRING, description: \\\"The description of the detail when examined.\\\" }\\n    },\\n    required: [\'key\', \'value\']\\n};\\n\\nconst roomSchema = {\\n    type: Type.OBJECT,\\n    properties: {\\n        id: { type: Type.STRING },\\n        name: { type: Type.STRING },\\n        description: { type: Type.STRING },\\n        exits: {\\n            type: Type.OBJECT,\\n            properties: {\\n                north: { type: Type.STRING, nullable: true },\\n                south: { type: Type.STRING, nullable: true },\\n                east: { type: Type.STRING, nullable: true },\\n                west: { type: Type.STRING, nullable: true },\\n            }\\n        },\\n        items: { type: Type.ARRAY, items: itemSchema },\\n        monster: {\\n            type: Type.OBJECT,\\n            properties: monsterSchema.properties,\\n            required: monsterSchema.required,\\n            nullable: true\\n        },\\n        details: { \\n            type: Type.ARRAY, \\n            items: detailSchema,\\n            description: \\\"An array of examinable scenery details in the room.\\\"\\n        },\\n    },\\n    required: [\'id\', \'name\', \'description\', \'exits\', \'items\']\\n};\\n\",\"TargetContent\":\"const roomSchema = {\\n    type: Type.OBJECT,\\n    properties: {\\n        id: { type: Type.STRING },\\n        name: { type: Type.STRING },\\n        description: { type: Type.STRING },\\n        exits: {\\n            type: Type.OBJECT,\\n            properties: {\\n                north: { type: Type.STRING, nullable: true },\\n                south: { type: Type.STRING, nullable: true },\\n                east: { type: Type.STRING, nullable: true },\\n                west: { type: Type.STRING, nullable: true },\\n            }\\n        },\\n        items: { type: Type.ARRAY, items: itemSchema },\\n        monster: { ...monsterSchema, nullable: true },\\n        // \'details\' is intentionally omitted from the schema because its dynamic keys\\n        // are not supported. The prompt instructs the AI to generate it correctly.\\n    },\\n    required: [\'id\', \'name\', \'description\', \'exits\', \'items\']\\n};\\n\"},{\"ReplacementContent\":\"export async function initializeGame(playerClass: PlayerClass): Promise<{ world: World, startingLocation: string, startingNarration: string }> {\\n    const aiInstance = getAI();\\n    \\n    const systemInstruction = `You are a creative and detailed Game Master for a classic text-based fantasy RPG. Your primary role is to generate a rich, interactive world and then manage the player\'s journey through it.`;\\n    \\n    const prompt = `Generate a small, unique, and compelling starting area for a new text adventure game. The player is a ${playerClass}.\\n    \\n    The area should consist of 3-5 interconnected rooms with a clear theme (e.g., \'a forgotten crypt\', \'a bandit hideout in a cave\', \'a crumbling wizard\'s tower\').\\n\\n    **CRITICAL: Environmental Puzzles & Obstacles**\\n    - You MUST include at least one environmental puzzle or obstacle.\\n    - Examples: A locked door requiring a key, a dark chasm needing a torch to cross, or a pile of rubble that needs clearing.\\n    - **IMPORTANT:** If a room has a locked or blocked exit, **DO NOT** include that direction in the \'exits\' object initially. \\n      - Instead, describe the blocked exit in the \'description\' (e.g., \\\"To the north, a heavy iron door stands locked.\\\").\\n      - Place the required key or tool (Item Type: \'Key\' or \'Quest\') in a different room or inside a container.\\n\\n    For the world structure, you MUST provide:\\n    1.  A \'rooms\' property which is an ARRAY of room objects.\\n    2.  Each room object in the array MUST contain:\\n        -   \'id\': A unique string ID (e.g., \'crypt_entrance\', \'hall_of_heroes\').\\n        -   \'name\': A short, evocative title (e.g., \\\"Sunken Tomb Entrance\\\").\\n        -   \'description\': A detailed, multi-sentence paragraph describing the room\'s atmosphere. Keep it under 100 words.\\n        -   \'exits\': An object where keys are directions (\'north\', \'south\', \'east\', \'west\') and values are the string IDs of the connected rooms.\\n        -   \'items\': An array of item objects. Items should have \'id\', \'name\', \'description\', and \'type\' (\'Weapon\', \'Armor\', \'Potion\', \'Key\', \'Quest\'). Weapons should have a \'value\' for damage, armor an \'armor\' value.\\n        -   \'monster\' (optional): A single monster object if the room is dangerous. Monsters need \'id\', \'name\', \'hp\', \'maxHp\', \'attack\', \'defense\', \'xp\', and a \'loot\' array.\\n        -   \'details\': An array of objects for examinable scenery, where each object has a \'key\' (e.g., \\\"altar\\\") and a \'value\' (description).\\n    3.  A \'startingLocation\' string, which must be the ID of one of the rooms you created.\\n    4.  A \'startingNarration\' string, which is a compelling description of the player\'s arrival in the starting location.\\n\\n    Your response must be ONLY the JSON object conforming to the schema. Do not include any other text or formatting.`;\\n\\n    // For world generation, we use a more powerful model for reliability\\n    const response = await aiInstance.models.generateContent({\\n        model: \'gemini-3.1-pro-preview\',\\n        contents: [{ parts: [{ text: prompt }] }],\\n        config: {\\n            systemInstruction: systemInstruction,\\n            responseMimeType: \\\"application/json\\\",\\n            responseSchema: worldSchema,\\n            maxOutputTokens: 4096,\\n        },\\n    });\\n\\n    const jsonText = response.text.trim();\\n    const parsed = cleanAndParseJson(jsonText);\\n    \\n    const worldRooms: Record<string, Room> = (parsed.rooms as any[]).reduce((acc, roomData) => {\\n        const room: Room = {\\n            ...roomData,\\n            details: {}\\n        };\\n        \\n        // Convert details array to record\\n        if (roomData.details && Array.isArray(roomData.details)) {\\n            const detailsRecord: Record<string, string> = {};\\n            roomData.details.forEach((d: any) => {\\n                if (d.key && d.value) {\\n                    detailsRecord[d.key] = d.value;\\n                }\\n            });\\n            room.details = detailsRecord;\\n        }\\n        \\n        acc[room.id] = room;\\n        return acc;\\n    }, {} as Record<string, Room>);\\n    \\n    const world: World = { rooms: worldRooms };\\n    \\n    // Initialize the chat session for the gameplay that follows\\n    chat = aiInstance.chats.create({\\n        model: \'gemini-3.1-pro-preview\',\\n        config: {\\n            systemInstruction: `You are the Game Master for a text-based RPG. You have two personas:\\n1.  **The Narrator**: An objective, descriptive, and engaging storyteller, writing in the second person (e.g., \\\"You see...\\\", \\\"You open the chest...\\\").\\n2.  **The Imp**: A sarcastic, wisecracking, cowardly voice in the player\'s head, inspired by Iago from Aladdin (a Gilbert Gottfried persona). It makes short, witty, and often unhelpful comments.\\n\\nYour response MUST strictly adhere to the provided JSON schema. Do not add extra commentary.`\\n        }\\n    });\\n\\n    return { world, startingLocation: parsed.startingLocation, startingNarration: parsed.startingNarration };\\n}\\n\\n/**\\n * Robustly cleans and parses JSON from the AI response.\\n */\\nfunction cleanAndParseJson(text: string): any {\\n    let cleaned = text.trim();\\n    // Remove markdown code blocks if present\\n    if (cleaned.startsWith(\'```\')) {\\n        cleaned = cleaned.replace(/^```(?:json)?\\\\n?/, \'\').replace(/\\\\n?```$/, \'\').trim();\\n    }\\n    \\n    try {\\n        return JSON.parse(cleaned);\\n    } catch (e) {\\n        console.error(\\\"Initial JSON parse failed, attempting repair...\\\", e);\\n        // Basic repair: try to close unclosed strings and structures\\n        let repaired = cleaned;\\n        \\n        // If it ends with a partial string, close it\\n        if ((repaired.match(/\\\"/g) || []).length % 2 !== 0) {\\n            repaired += \'\\\"\';\\n        }\\n        \\n        // Close braces and brackets\\n        const openBraces = (repaired.match(/\\\\{/g) || []).length;\\n        const closeBraces = (repaired.match(/\\\\}/g) || []).length;\\n        for (let i = 0; i < openBraces - closeBraces; i++) repaired += \'}\';\\n        \\n        const openBrackets = (repaired.match(/\\\\[/g) || []).length;\\n        const closeBrackets = (repaired.match(/\\\\]/g) || []).length;\\n        for (let i = 0; i < openBrackets - closeBrackets; i++) repaired += \']\';\\n        \\n        try {\\n            return JSON.parse(repaired);\\n        } catch (e2) {\\n            console.error(\\\"Repair failed:\\\", e2);\\n            throw e; // Throw original error if repair fails\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\",\"TargetContent\":\"export async function initializeGame(playerClass: PlayerClass): Promise<{ world: World, startingLocation: string, startingNarration: string }> {\\n    const aiInstance = getAI();\\n    \\n    const systemInstruction = `You are a creative and detailed Game Master for a classic text-based fantasy RPG. Your primary role is to generate a rich, interactive world and then manage the player\'s journey through it.`;\\n    \\n    const prompt = `Generate a small, unique, and compelling starting area for a new text adventure game. The player is a ${playerClass}.\\n    \\n    The area should consist of 3-5 interconnected rooms with a clear theme (e.g., \'a forgotten crypt\', \'a bandit hideout in a cave\', \'a crumbling wizard\'s tower\').\\n\\n    **CRITICAL: Environmental Puzzles & Obstacles**\\n    - You MUST include at least one environmental puzzle or obstacle.\\n    - Examples: A locked door requiring a key, a dark chasm needing a torch to cross, or a pile of rubble that needs clearing.\\n    - **IMPORTANT:** If a room has a locked or blocked exit, **DO NOT** include that direction in the \'exits\' object initially. \\n      - Instead, describe the blocked exit in the \'description\' (e.g., \\\"To the north, a heavy iron door stands locked.\\\").\\n      - Place the required key or tool (Item Type: \'Key\' or \'Quest\') in a different room or inside a container.\\n\\n    For the world structure, you MUST provide:\\n    1.  A \'rooms\' property which is an ARRAY of room objects.\\n    2.  Each room object in the array MUST contain:\\n        -   \'id\': A unique string ID (e.g., \'crypt_entrance\', \'hall_of_heroes\').\\n        -   \'name\': A short, evocative title (e.g., \\\"Sunken Tomb Entrance\\\").\\n        -   \'description\': A detailed, multi-sentence paragraph describing the room\'s atmosphere, appearance, and key features.\\n        -   \'exits\': An object where keys are directions (\'north\', \'south\', \'east\', \'west\') and values are the string IDs of the connected rooms.\\n        -   \'items\': An array of item objects. Items should have \'id\', \'name\', \'description\', and \'type\' (\'Weapon\', \'Armor\', \'Potion\', \'Key\', \'Quest\'). Weapons should have a \'value\' for damage, armor an \'armor\' value.\\n        -   \'monster\' (optional): A single monster object if the room is dangerous. Monsters need \'id\', \'name\', \'hp\', \'maxHp\', \'attack\', \'defense\', \'xp\', and a \'loot\' array.\\n        -   \'details\' (optional): An object for examinable scenery, where keys are keywords (e.g., \\\"altar\\\") and values are their descriptions.\\n    3.  A \'startingLocation\' string, which must be the ID of one of the rooms you created.\\n    4.  A \'startingNarration\' string, which is a compelling description of the player\'s arrival in the starting location.\\n\\n    Your response must be ONLY the JSON object conforming to the schema. Do not include any other text or formatting.`;\\n\\n    // For world generation, we don\'t use a chat. It\'s a one-off request.\\n    const response = await aiInstance.models.generateContent({\\n        model: \'gemini-2.5-flash\',\\n        contents: [{ parts: [{ text: prompt }] }],\\n        config: {\\n            systemInstruction: systemInstruction,\\n            responseMimeType: \\\"application/json\\\",\\n            responseSchema: worldSchema,\\n        },\\n    });\\n\\n    const jsonText = response.text.trim();\\n    const parsed: { rooms: Room[], startingLocation: string, startingNarration: string } = JSON.parse(jsonText);\\n    \\n    const worldRooms: Record<string, Room> = parsed.rooms.reduce((acc, room) => {\\n        acc[room.id] = room;\\n        return acc;\\n    }, {} as Record<string, Room>);\\n    \\n    const world: World = { rooms: worldRooms };\\n    \\n    // Initialize the chat session for the gameplay that follows\\n    chat = aiInstance.chats.create({\\n        model: \'gemini-2.5-flash\',\\n        config: {\\n            systemInstruction: `You are the Game Master for a text-based RPG. You have two personas:\\n1.  **The Narrator**: An objective, descriptive, and engaging storyteller, writing in the second person (e.g., \\\"You see...\\\", \\\"You open the chest...\\\").\\n2.  **The Imp**: A sarcastic, wisecracking, cowardly voice in the player\'s head, inspired by Iago from Aladdin (a Gilbert Gottfried persona). It makes short, witty, and often unhelpful comments.\\n\\nYour response MUST strictly adhere to the provided JSON schema. Do not add extra commentary.`\\n        }\\n    });\\n\\n    return { world, startingLocation: parsed.startingLocation, startingNarration: parsed.startingNarration };\\n}\\n\"},{\"ReplacementContent\":\"    try {\\n        const response = await chat.sendMessage({\\n            message: prompt,\\n            config: {\\n                responseMimeType: \\\"application/json\\\",\\n                responseSchema: turnSchema,\\n                maxOutputTokens: 2048,\\n            }\\n        });\\n\\n        const jsonText = response.text.trim();\\n        return cleanAndParseJson(jsonText) as GameStateUpdate;\\n\\n    } catch (error) {\\n\",\"TargetContent\":\"    try {\\n        const response = await chat.sendMessage({\\n            message: prompt,\\n            config: {\\n                responseMimeType: \\\"application/json\\\",\\n                responseSchema: turnSchema,\\n            }\\n        });\\n\\n        const jsonText = response.text.trim();\\n        return JSON.parse(jsonText) as GameStateUpdate;\\n\\n    } catch (error) {\\n\"},{\"ReplacementContent\":\"    try {\\n        const response = await aiInstance.models.generateContent({\\n            model: \'gemini-3-flash-preview\',\\n            contents: [{ parts: [{ text: prompt }] }],\\n            config: { systemInstruction },\\n        });\\n        return response.text.trim().replace(/,/g, \'\'); // Ensure no commas\\n    } catch (error) {\\n\",\"TargetContent\":\"    try {\\n        const response = await aiInstance.models.generateContent({\\n            model: \'gemini-2.5-flash\',\\n            contents: [{ parts: [{ text: prompt }] }],\\n            config: { systemInstruction },\\n        });\\n        return response.text.trim().replace(/,/g, \'\'); // Ensure no commas\\n    } catch (error) {\\n\"},{\"ReplacementContent\":\"    try {\\n        const response = await aiInstance.models.generateContent({\\n            model: \'gemini-3-flash-preview\',\\n            contents: [{ parts: [{ text: prompt }] }],\\n            config: {\\n                systemInstruction: systemInstruction,\\n            },\\n        });\\n        return response.text.trim();\\n    } catch (error) {\\n\",\"TargetContent\":\"    try {\\n        const response = await aiInstance.models.generateContent({\\n            model: \'gemini-2.5-flash\',\\n            contents: [{ parts: [{ text: prompt }] }],\\n            config: {\\n                systemInstruction: systemInstruction,\\n            },\\n        });\\n        return response.text.trim();\\n    } catch (error) {\\n\"}],\"TargetFile\":\"/services/aiService.ts\"}"
