    thinking: "**Analyzing the Error Source**\n\nI\'ve pinpointed the `try-catch` block handling `chat.sendMessage` failures, confirming its return of the expected fallback message. However, the user still sees \"A mysterious force prevented that action...\". This means `App.tsx`\'s overarching `catch` block is being triggered instead, indicating a deeper issue I need to explore.\n\n\n**Investigating ProcessCommand Failure**\n\nI\'m now focusing on `processCommand`, suspecting it\'s the source of the `App.tsx`\'s catch. Specifically, the error is within `engine.ts` in `processPlayerTurn`, if `update.player` is manipulated, I need to know why and under what conditions. The check around `oldMonsterHp` seems sound. The problem must be elsewhere. I\'ll need to go deeper into its logic, focusing on the conditions.\n\n\n**Uncovering a New Error**\n\nI think I\'ve found a critical vulnerability. The AI could be setting `newState.player.location` to an invalid `room` ID. This would lead to a runtime error when trying to access `newState.world.rooms[currentRoomId]`, specifically in lines 128-137 of `engine.ts`. The access to `currentRoom.exits` when `currentRoom` is undefined is the most likely culprit. The AI, in its updates to `update.player.location`, might be introducing the hallucinated room IDs, it might have new room data or have a room that is not yet fully defined or initialized. This aligns with the observed \"mysterious force\" error. I need to validate the integrity of `newState.player.location` before using it.\n\n\n**Revisiting State Updates**\n\nI\'m now re-examining `App.tsx`\'s `handleCommand`, specifically line 211\'s `processCommand` invocation. I\'m focusing on `commandState` creation, as it uses spread syntax from `state`. If `state` is corrupt, subsequent command failures are expected. The user\'s \"after anything I enter\" remark strengthens this hypothesis. I\'ll need to carefully examine how the state is initialized, updated, and potentially corrupted. I will also investigate if a change in models, from `gemini-3.1-pro-preview` to `gemini-3-flash-preview` is a better fit. I have some concerns from my most recent observations.\n\n\n"
