    response: "I have implemented several critical fixes to address the \"mysterious force\" error and improve the overall stability of the game:\n\n1.  **Resilient AI Initialization**: I moved the AI initialization logic inside the error-handling blocks. Previously, if you refreshed the page and tried to resume a game, the AI \"chat\" would be uninitialized, causing a crash. Now, the game automatically re-establishes the connection if it\'s missing.\n2.  **Robust Room Navigation**: I added a safety check in the game engine. If the AI hallucinates a room that doesn\'t exist in the world (a common issue with LLMs), the engine will now catch this and keep you in your current room rather than crashing the application.\n3.  **Enhanced Error Diagnostics**: I\'ve updated the error handling to provide more detailed logs in the developer console. If a \"mysterious force\" does occur, it will now specifically check for common issues like a missing API key and provide a more helpful message.\n4.  **Graceful Fallbacks**: If the AI service fails for any reason (network issues, safety filters, etc.), the game will now provide a narrative fallback (\"The fabric of reality shimmers...\") instead of showing a generic error message, allowing you to try your action again.\n\nThese changes should resolve the persistent error you were seeing after entering commands."
